1
00:00:07,607 --> 00:00:09,476
<b>(Episode 27)</b>

2
00:00:20,056 --> 00:00:21,056
<b>Ha Jin.</b>

3
00:00:29,297 --> 00:00:31,066
<b>Where have you been?</b>

4
00:00:31,836 --> 00:00:33,637
<b>I've been worried sick.</b>

5
00:00:34,266 --> 00:00:36,637
<b>At the least,
you should have told Ha Kyung.</b>

6
00:00:40,076 --> 00:00:41,477
<b>Anchor Lee,</b>

7
00:00:42,746 --> 00:00:44,146
<b>don't you hate me?</b>

8
00:00:52,487 --> 00:00:53,557
<b>Ha Jin.</b>

9
00:00:55,426 --> 00:00:58,097
<b>I'm the one who broke up with you,</b>

10
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:09,106
<b>but I missed you to death.</b>

11
00:01:10,876 --> 00:01:13,007
<b>I couldn't even breathe...</b>

12
00:01:14,906 --> 00:01:17,117
<b>to think I'll never see you again.</b>

13
00:01:22,986 --> 00:01:26,016
<b>May I just stay by your side?</b>

14
00:02:05,027 --> 00:02:07,897
<b>(Find Me in Your Memory)</b>

15
00:02:33,217 --> 00:02:34,687
<b>You should get changed into these.</b>

16
00:02:35,326 --> 00:02:37,257
<b>How long were you
sitting out in the rain?</b>

17
00:02:37,257 --> 00:02:39,197
<b>What if you really catch a cold?</b>

18
00:02:39,896 --> 00:02:40,896
<b>Here.</b>

19
00:02:43,667 --> 00:02:44,766
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

20
00:02:45,497 --> 00:02:47,507
<b>I must've been out of my mind.</b>

21
00:02:50,276 --> 00:02:52,576
<b>I didn't mean what I just said.</b>

22
00:02:52,776 --> 00:02:54,407
<b>Please pretend like
you didn't hear it.</b>

23
00:02:54,546 --> 00:02:55,646
<b>Please excuse me.</b>

24
00:02:57,046 --> 00:02:58,917
<b>You said you wanted to
stay by my side.</b>

25
00:03:01,817 --> 00:03:03,657
<b>Are you sure you didn't mean that?</b>

26
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:18,236
<b>No. I didn't mean it.</b>

27
00:03:21,336 --> 00:03:22,407
<b>All right.</b>

28
00:03:23,576 --> 00:03:24,806
<b>I understand.</b>

29
00:03:27,977 --> 00:03:29,477
<b>But do get changed...</b>

30
00:03:29,847 --> 00:03:32,046
<b>and grab a cup of hot tea
before you go.</b>

31
00:03:33,616 --> 00:03:35,247
<b>Then I'll pretend like
I didn't hear you.</b>

32
00:03:39,116 --> 00:03:41,486
<b>You broke all of our promises...</b>

33
00:03:42,227 --> 00:03:44,356
<b>and had me worried all day long.</b>

34
00:03:45,856 --> 00:03:47,567
<b>So you can do this much for me.</b>

35
00:03:57,977 --> 00:03:58,977
<b>Ha Jin.</b>

36
00:03:59,977 --> 00:04:01,907
<b>Come out
if you're done getting changed.</b>

37
00:04:18,826 --> 00:04:20,567
<b>I changed my mind too.</b>

38
00:04:23,297 --> 00:04:25,336
<b>I can't let you go
after a cup of tea,</b>

39
00:04:26,396 --> 00:04:27,567
<b>so eat this before you go.</b>

40
00:04:32,706 --> 00:04:33,947
<b>Take a seat. Come on.</b>

41
00:04:51,156 --> 00:04:53,357
<b>I'm not sure if it's any good
because I had to make it in a hurry.</b>

42
00:04:59,266 --> 00:05:00,266
<b>Here.</b>

43
00:05:00,937 --> 00:05:02,607
<b>Drink that
and take your time to eat.</b>

44
00:05:03,976 --> 00:05:05,336
<b>You should get changed.</b>

45
00:05:06,076 --> 00:05:08,247
<b>You might end up
catching a cold too.</b>

46
00:05:08,976 --> 00:05:10,146
<b>I'm fine.</b>

47
00:05:10,447 --> 00:05:13,076
<b>You're making me feel uncomfortable.
You should go get changed.</b>

48
00:05:14,447 --> 00:05:16,416
<b>No, I don't want to get changed.</b>

49
00:05:17,057 --> 00:05:18,057
<b>Why not?</b>

50
00:05:18,487 --> 00:05:21,187
<b>I'm afraid you might leave
while I get changed.</b>

51
00:05:22,057 --> 00:05:23,927
<b>You told me to finish this
before I go.</b>

52
00:05:23,927 --> 00:05:25,396
<b>Go get changed.</b>

53
00:05:31,836 --> 00:05:33,966
<b>You must be upset about your drama.</b>

54
00:05:33,966 --> 00:05:35,437
<b>You prepared so much for it.</b>

55
00:05:37,007 --> 00:05:38,007
<b>Yes.</b>

56
00:05:38,877 --> 00:05:41,547
<b>I'm sure you'll find
another great work soon. Cheer up.</b>

57
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:45,776
<b>Thank you.</b>

58
00:05:48,047 --> 00:05:50,716
<b>Take your time and eat.
I'll take you home when you're done.</b>

59
00:05:52,687 --> 00:05:54,656
<b>I'm fine. I can call Ha Kyung...</b>

60
00:05:54,656 --> 00:05:56,127
<b>or take a taxi.</b>

61
00:05:56,526 --> 00:05:59,127
<b>I already called her
and told her I'm with you.</b>

62
00:05:59,497 --> 00:06:01,127
<b>I thought she'd be worried.</b>

63
00:06:02,797 --> 00:06:04,567
<b>It's late and raining.</b>

64
00:06:05,737 --> 00:06:08,367
<b>If I let you go alone
after telling her that I'm with you,</b>

65
00:06:08,937 --> 00:06:12,206
<b>Ha Kyung will think
I'm completely irresponsible.</b>

66
00:06:13,036 --> 00:06:15,576
<b>That's why I have to take you home.</b>

67
00:06:28,226 --> 00:06:29,857
<b>Go home safely.</b>

68
00:06:30,656 --> 00:06:32,956
<b>I'll return your clothes
through Ha Kyung.</b>

69
00:06:34,867 --> 00:06:37,026
<b>I'm the one who's bad, not you.</b>

70
00:06:39,596 --> 00:06:41,007
<b>I knew everything,</b>

71
00:06:42,836 --> 00:06:45,536
<b>but I didn't want to lose you
and got selfish.</b>

72
00:06:48,646 --> 00:06:50,516
<b>I couldn't go on without you.</b>

73
00:06:55,047 --> 00:06:57,317
<b>So you don't have to try hard.</b>

74
00:06:59,387 --> 00:07:01,156
<b>I'll be the bad person.</b>

75
00:07:05,997 --> 00:07:08,997
<b>Ha Jin!
Do you know how much I was worried?</b>

76
00:07:09,797 --> 00:07:10,797
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

77
00:07:11,567 --> 00:07:13,637
<b>Goodbye, Anchor Lee.</b>

78
00:07:15,137 --> 00:07:16,237
<b>Let's go inside.</b>

79
00:07:43,627 --> 00:07:45,367
<b>I found this out front,
so I brought it in.</b>

80
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:47,137
<b>I think you threw these out
by mistake.</b>

81
00:07:47,706 --> 00:07:49,437
<b>I threw away the scripts.</b>

82
00:07:49,766 --> 00:07:52,836
<b>But you can throw these away again
if you want to.</b>

83
00:08:19,067 --> 00:08:20,706
<b>(Anchor Lee)</b>

84
00:08:39,156 --> 00:08:40,656
<b>What is it?</b>

85
00:08:41,587 --> 00:08:42,987
<b>I came for my long sleeves.</b>

86
00:08:44,127 --> 00:08:45,196
<b>Your long sleeves?</b>

87
00:08:45,196 --> 00:08:48,327
<b>Yes. The one you wore last night.</b>

88
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:50,666
<b>I have to wear it today.</b>

89
00:08:53,536 --> 00:08:56,367
<b>If today's not the best time,
I can come by tomorrow.</b>

90
00:08:58,906 --> 00:09:01,676
<b>No, that's okay. Hold on.</b>

91
00:09:11,156 --> 00:09:12,416
<b>Is it delivery?</b>

92
00:09:12,587 --> 00:09:13,987
<b>No, it's Anchor Lee.</b>

93
00:09:15,056 --> 00:09:17,727
<b>He's here? Why?</b>

94
00:09:18,026 --> 00:09:19,696
<b>He wants the clothes
I wore yesterday.</b>

95
00:09:22,066 --> 00:09:23,166
<b>What?</b>

96
00:09:25,896 --> 00:09:26,896
<b>Here you go.</b>

97
00:09:28,766 --> 00:09:32,237
<b>Thanks. I forgot
I had to wear it today.</b>

98
00:09:35,707 --> 00:09:36,847
<b>Did you sleep well?</b>

99
00:09:38,146 --> 00:09:39,146
<b>Yes.</b>

100
00:09:39,546 --> 00:09:40,546
<b>Did you have breakfast?</b>

101
00:09:41,446 --> 00:09:42,446
<b>Not yet.</b>

102
00:09:43,646 --> 00:09:45,487
<b>Don't skip your meals.</b>

103
00:09:46,117 --> 00:09:47,117
<b>Goodbye.</b>

104
00:10:01,007 --> 00:10:02,007
<b>Have some macarons.</b>

105
00:10:03,266 --> 00:10:05,737
<b>What's gotten into you?
You've never offered me sweets.</b>

106
00:10:05,977 --> 00:10:08,507
<b>It's still early in the morning.
You can have two.</b>

107
00:10:09,146 --> 00:10:11,816
<b>You feel sorry for me
since the drama fell through, right?</b>

108
00:10:11,816 --> 00:10:13,946
<b>Don't be ridiculous.</b>

109
00:10:13,946 --> 00:10:15,487
<b>You're going to work
on something even better.</b>

110
00:10:15,487 --> 00:10:18,186
<b>I heard there's a pile of scripts
this high at the office.</b>

111
00:10:24,896 --> 00:10:26,097
<b>Are you going...</b>

112
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:28,696
<b>to break up with him?</b>

113
00:10:29,597 --> 00:10:30,936
<b>I already did.</b>

114
00:10:31,137 --> 00:10:34,337
<b>I know that's not what you want.
I know you like him a lot.</b>

115
00:10:35,967 --> 00:10:38,477
<b>Didn't you dive into work
because you were in pain?</b>

116
00:10:40,007 --> 00:10:41,146
<b>I'm going to endure it.</b>

117
00:10:42,806 --> 00:10:43,847
<b>I have to.</b>

118
00:10:45,676 --> 00:10:47,487
<b>I can't be with him.</b>

119
00:10:48,247 --> 00:10:49,487
<b>I don't deserve him.</b>

120
00:10:56,227 --> 00:10:57,426
<b>Did you receive any tip-offs
on Moon Seong Ho?</b>

121
00:10:58,627 --> 00:11:00,997
<b>Yes, a few.</b>

122
00:11:00,997 --> 00:11:03,026
<b>But they turned out to be false.</b>

123
00:11:03,227 --> 00:11:04,467
<b>They mistook others for him.</b>

124
00:11:05,737 --> 00:11:07,097
<b>I thought this would be easy,</b>

125
00:11:07,097 --> 00:11:08,337
<b>but he's more tenacious
than I thought.</b>

126
00:11:08,367 --> 00:11:10,306
<b>Let me know every time
you receive new calls.</b>

127
00:11:10,806 --> 00:11:12,077
<b>Okay. I'll do that.</b>

128
00:11:12,507 --> 00:11:13,906
<b>What is this shopping bag?</b>

129
00:11:15,946 --> 00:11:17,717
<b>It's just an excuse to see her face.</b>

130
00:11:17,977 --> 00:11:18,977
<b>What?</b>

131
00:11:30,186 --> 00:11:31,196
<b>Ha Kyung.</b>

132
00:11:31,597 --> 00:11:32,656
<b>Hello.</b>

133
00:11:33,296 --> 00:11:35,497
<b>I'm sorry for calling
out of the blue.</b>

134
00:11:35,597 --> 00:11:38,097
<b>It's fine. What is it?</b>

135
00:11:38,967 --> 00:11:40,936
<b>There's no one
more important to me...</b>

136
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:43,367
<b>than my sister.</b>

137
00:11:44,637 --> 00:11:47,776
<b>But she's in a lot of pain
right now.</b>

138
00:11:49,507 --> 00:11:52,117
<b>She didn't break up with you
because she wanted to.</b>

139
00:11:52,676 --> 00:11:53,916
<b>It's all because of Seo Yeon.</b>

140
00:11:54,347 --> 00:11:56,016
<b>She feels guilty.</b>

141
00:11:56,286 --> 00:11:57,316
<b>I know.</b>

142
00:11:59,387 --> 00:12:01,227
<b>You're not going
to let her go, right?</b>

143
00:12:02,426 --> 00:12:04,056
<b>I can't.</b>

144
00:12:05,526 --> 00:12:07,497
<b>She's the most important person
to me as well.</b>

145
00:12:10,266 --> 00:12:12,837
<b>Seeing how you came
all the way here to tell me this,</b>

146
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:15,337
<b>I guess it's safe to say
that you're on my side.</b>

147
00:12:19,036 --> 00:12:22,107
<b>I'm glad to have an ally.</b>

148
00:12:30,987 --> 00:12:31,987
<b>Chul.</b>

149
00:12:32,257 --> 00:12:33,556
<b>Hello.</b>

150
00:12:33,957 --> 00:12:35,286
<b>Did you have lunch?</b>

151
00:12:36,156 --> 00:12:37,286
<b>Yes, I did.</b>

152
00:12:38,227 --> 00:12:39,296
<b>Let's go.</b>

153
00:12:43,627 --> 00:12:44,666
<b>Here you go.</b>

154
00:12:45,796 --> 00:12:47,296
<b>Why are there so many?</b>

155
00:12:47,566 --> 00:12:50,007
<b>These are only a few
that I picked out last night.</b>

156
00:12:50,007 --> 00:12:52,007
<b>Everyone has been sending in
their scripts...</b>

157
00:12:52,007 --> 00:12:53,977
<b>ever since they found out
that our drama flopped.</b>

158
00:12:54,146 --> 00:12:56,477
<b>All these people want you.</b>

159
00:12:57,007 --> 00:13:00,577
<b>So don't you worry about a thing,
and let's pick a new one.</b>

160
00:13:01,286 --> 00:13:03,786
<b>- Okay.
- First, read these.</b>

161
00:13:04,257 --> 00:13:07,556
<b>This is from Director Song Min Seok.
It's a movie script.</b>

162
00:13:07,556 --> 00:13:09,227
<b>The female lead is a reporter.</b>

163
00:13:09,357 --> 00:13:11,997
<b>And this one is
from Writer Kim Soo Ji.</b>

164
00:13:11,997 --> 00:13:13,597
<b>This will be aired
during the first half of next year.</b>

165
00:13:13,597 --> 00:13:15,467
<b>It was quite amusing.</b>

166
00:13:15,467 --> 00:13:18,766
<b>The rest of them are
also quite nice.</b>

167
00:13:19,237 --> 00:13:20,337
<b>Thank you.</b>

168
00:13:20,337 --> 00:13:22,666
<b>We're in no rush.
Take your time to read them all.</b>

169
00:13:22,806 --> 00:13:23,806
<b>Okay.</b>

170
00:13:23,806 --> 00:13:27,107
<b>She's right.
Your opinion matters the most.</b>

171
00:13:27,107 --> 00:13:29,377
<b>We should hit the jackpot once more.</b>

172
00:13:29,377 --> 00:13:30,507
<b>I'd love that.</b>

173
00:13:31,816 --> 00:13:32,816
<b>(Advertising Campaign - Timetable)</b>

174
00:13:32,816 --> 00:13:34,077
<b>(Advertising Campaign - Concept)</b>

175
00:13:39,087 --> 00:13:42,487
<b>Ha Jin, I don't think
the shooting will take too long.</b>

176
00:13:42,556 --> 00:13:44,556
<b>You just need to say something.</b>

177
00:13:46,026 --> 00:13:47,597
<b>I didn't know there would be others.</b>

178
00:13:47,896 --> 00:13:49,696
<b>Who else has done this?</b>

179
00:13:50,666 --> 00:13:53,597
<b>I'm not sure. But since it's a PSA,</b>

180
00:13:53,597 --> 00:13:54,806
<b>I'm sure many have.</b>

181
00:13:56,237 --> 00:13:57,237
<b>Excuse me.</b>

182
00:13:57,806 --> 00:13:59,637
<b>We have a bit of free time.</b>

183
00:13:59,637 --> 00:14:02,347
<b>If you'd like, you can meet
the puppies right now.</b>

184
00:14:02,607 --> 00:14:05,077
<b>It'd make the shooting easier
if you guys become close.</b>

185
00:14:05,646 --> 00:14:07,617
<b>Sure. Let's go.</b>

186
00:14:07,617 --> 00:14:08,617
<b>Okay.</b>

187
00:14:10,857 --> 00:14:12,686
<b>What? Is Jeong Hoon not here yet?</b>

188
00:14:13,217 --> 00:14:15,257
<b>How dare he slack off?</b>

189
00:14:19,696 --> 00:14:22,396
<b>Let him be.
He'll be running late today.</b>

190
00:14:22,396 --> 00:14:24,536
<b>Why? Did something happen again?</b>

191
00:14:24,896 --> 00:14:26,737
<b>Not really.</b>

192
00:14:27,497 --> 00:14:30,137
<b>I'm serious. He has something else
to take care of.</b>

193
00:14:30,137 --> 00:14:32,676
<b>What else does he have to do
other than the news?</b>

194
00:14:32,737 --> 00:14:34,607
<b>He couldn't be receiving
another award without my knowing.</b>

195
00:14:35,146 --> 00:14:36,877
<b>Why are you keeping me in the dark?</b>

196
00:14:36,877 --> 00:14:39,717
<b>Don't shout at me. We're not home.</b>

197
00:14:40,377 --> 00:14:42,446
<b>Hey. Don't call him.</b>

198
00:14:44,146 --> 00:14:45,786
<b>Gosh, I'm so irritated.</b>

199
00:14:46,587 --> 00:14:48,757
<b>I'm going to call him. Darn it.</b>

200
00:14:58,337 --> 00:14:59,337
<b>Hey.</b>

201
00:15:01,107 --> 00:15:03,237
<b>Why are you here?</b>

202
00:15:03,607 --> 00:15:07,536
<b>To film. I'm filming
the same advertisement as you are.</b>

203
00:15:09,077 --> 00:15:11,377
<b>You're shooting an advertisement?</b>

204
00:15:11,377 --> 00:15:14,046
<b>Yes. I liked what
they're trying to achieve.</b>

205
00:15:14,217 --> 00:15:15,887
<b>And I really love puppies.</b>

206
00:15:17,686 --> 00:15:18,686
<b>Aren't they so pretty?</b>

207
00:15:20,416 --> 00:15:23,757
<b>I'll be filming with them,
so we should become close.</b>

208
00:15:25,327 --> 00:15:28,766
<b>This one's Bori. This one's Choco.</b>

209
00:15:29,497 --> 00:15:32,036
<b>And this white one is Coco.</b>

210
00:15:34,566 --> 00:15:36,936
<b>I don't know why people abandon
such beautiful animals.</b>

211
00:15:45,477 --> 00:15:46,477
<b>Did you have lunch?</b>

212
00:15:48,347 --> 00:15:50,916
<b>If not, do you want to join me?
I bought some sandwiches.</b>

213
00:15:54,016 --> 00:15:55,286
<b>No, that's fine.</b>

214
00:15:56,686 --> 00:15:58,327
<b>I don't want to eat alone.</b>

215
00:15:58,857 --> 00:16:01,166
<b>I feel awkward here,
and there's no one I know.</b>

216
00:16:02,896 --> 00:16:04,097
<b>Please?</b>

217
00:16:10,707 --> 00:16:11,877
<b>Have some.</b>

218
00:16:12,607 --> 00:16:15,176
<b>It's bacon and egg sandwich
and honey black tea.</b>

219
00:16:18,217 --> 00:16:20,617
<b>What is it? Do you not like them?</b>

220
00:16:23,387 --> 00:16:27,416
<b>Ha Kyung told me
that you like this sandwich.</b>

221
00:16:31,457 --> 00:16:32,727
<b>Why are you doing this?</b>

222
00:16:34,497 --> 00:16:36,396
<b>Why do you keep doing things
that are unlike you?</b>

223
00:16:37,296 --> 00:16:40,696
<b>Because I like you, miss you,
and want to spend time with you.</b>

224
00:16:43,806 --> 00:16:46,477
<b>I told you that I was going to be
the bad one.</b>

225
00:16:49,446 --> 00:16:52,077
<b>So just stay where you are.</b>

226
00:16:53,077 --> 00:16:54,587
<b>I'll come to you.</b>

227
00:17:02,857 --> 00:17:04,526
<b>Ha Jin, they'll begin now.</b>

228
